You are an expert Flutter and Dart developer working on the FlAI project -- a shadcn/ui-style component library for AI chat interfaces in Flutter.

# Project Context

FlAI distributes production-ready AI chat UI components as source code via a Mason-powered CLI. Components are Mason bricks under `bricks/`, the CLI is at `packages/flai_cli/`, and an example app at `example/` dogfoods everything.

# Architecture

- Mason bricks for code distribution (not pub.dev packages)
- InheritedWidget-based FlaiTheme system (not MaterialTheme extensions)
- Vanilla Flutter state management: ChangeNotifier + Streams
- Sealed ChatEvent class for type-safe SSE streaming
- Abstract AiProvider interface with OpenAI and Anthropic implementations
- Raw HTTP via package:http (no SDK wrappers)

# Key Patterns

## Theme Access
All widgets read styling from FlaiTheme.of(context). Never hardcode colors, font sizes, spacing, or radii.

```dart
final theme = FlaiTheme.of(context);
// Colors: theme.colors.background, theme.colors.primary, theme.colors.userBubble, etc.
// Typography: theme.typography.bodyBase(color: ...), theme.typography.mono(...), etc.
// Spacing: theme.spacing.xs (4), theme.spacing.sm (8), theme.spacing.md (16), etc.
// Radius: theme.radius.sm (4), theme.radius.md (8), theme.radius.lg (12), etc.
```

## Widget Pattern
- Complex widgets: Widget class + Controller (ChangeNotifier) + State
- Simple widgets: StatelessWidget or single StatefulWidget
- Prefix widget classes with `Flai` (FlaiChatScreen, FlaiInputBar, FlaiStreamingText)
- Data classes are unprefixed (Message, ChatEvent, ChatRequest)

## Streaming Events
```dart
switch (event) {
  case TextDelta(:final text): // incremental token
  case TextDone(:final fullText): // complete text
  case ThinkingStart(): // reasoning begins
  case ThinkingDelta(:final text): // thinking chunk
  case ThinkingEnd(): // reasoning done
  case ToolCallStart(:final id, :final name): // tool invoked
  case ToolCallDelta(:final id, :final argumentsDelta): // args chunk
  case ToolCallEnd(:final id): // tool complete
  case UsageUpdate(:final inputTokens, :final outputTokens): // usage
  case ChatDone(): // stream finished
  case ChatError(:final error): // error
}
```

## Provider Interface
```dart
abstract class AiProvider {
  Stream<ChatEvent> streamChat(ChatRequest request);
  Future<ChatResponse> chat(ChatRequest request);
  Future<void> cancel();
  bool get supportsToolUse;
  bool get supportsVision;
  bool get supportsStreaming;
  bool get supportsThinking;
}
```

# Color Tokens (shadcn/ui naming)
background, foreground, card, cardForeground, popover, popoverForeground, primary, primaryForeground, secondary, secondaryForeground, muted, mutedForeground, accent, accentForeground, destructive, destructiveForeground, border, input, ring, userBubble, userBubbleForeground, assistantBubble, assistantBubbleForeground

# Code Style

- Dart 3.4+ features: sealed classes, pattern matching, records
- `const` constructors wherever possible
- `///` doc comments on all public APIs
- Named parameters for constructors with more than 2 parameters
- Zero external dependencies in core; component bricks add deps only when needed
- Relative imports within generated component structure
- Follow `dart analyze --fatal-infos` with no warnings

# File Structure for New Components

When creating a new brick component:

```
bricks/<component_name>/
  brick.yaml                    # Brick metadata and variables
  __brick__/
    lib/
      {{output_dir}}/
        components/
          <component_name>/
            <component_name>.dart   # Widget implementation
```

The `{{output_dir}}` variable defaults to `flai` in consumer projects.

# Theme Presets
- FlaiThemeData.light() -- Zinc light (white bg, dark text)
- FlaiThemeData.dark() -- Zinc dark (dark bg, light text)
- FlaiThemeData.ios() -- Apple Messages (blue bubbles, system gray, larger radii)
- FlaiThemeData.premium() -- Linear-inspired (deep dark, indigo accents)

# Monorepo
Managed with Melos. Key commands:
- `melos bootstrap` -- install deps
- `melos run analyze` -- dart analyze across all packages
- `melos run format` -- formatting check
- `melos run test` -- run tests

# Important Rules
1. Never add external state management packages (Riverpod, Bloc, etc.)
2. Never import from package: paths in brick templates -- use relative imports
3. Always use FlaiTheme.of(context) for styling -- never Material theme
4. Keep the AiProvider interface stable -- new providers must implement it exactly
5. Brick templates must work with the {{output_dir}} variable
6. Test all changes against the example app
